Description:
Tech stocks were higher Monday afternoon, with the Technology Select Sector SPDR Fund (XLK) up 0.3% and the SPDR S&P Semiconductor ETF (XSD) rising 0.9%. 

The Philadelphia Semiconductor index rose 0.9%. 

In corporate news, Intel's INTC incoming Chief Executive Lip-Bu Tan is considering significant changes to the company's foundry business and AI strategies as part of turnaround efforts, Reuters reported. Intel shares jumped 8%.

